cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.IR 

This paper deals with natural language generation and specifically focuses on generating interesting story endings. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes models that use attention mechanisms and promote the generation of non-generic words, which are techniques commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper uses neural generative models, which are a subset of neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper deals with text generation and language modeling, which are topics commonly studied in information retrieval (cs.IR).
